values: went to decatur monday through yesterday, there were alot of people i would love to see... sadly didnt have time to... i tripped balls tho... but the whole time i was fucked up, i kept thinking i was back home in chicago, also did some things im not proud of.

i am now a slave to wendys... where i am the only white person there, not that there is a problem with that. i just dont like sticking out like a sore thumb... i am 19 now as of monday. betty killed my hair with blue black hair dye. it looks good, she did me, bill and andrew with the same bottle. andrews turned out just dark blue. betty had planned a whole b-day weekend for me last weekend. a party with more alcohol than i can shake a stick at, then me and her and andrew get really stoned and see sin city. but there was a lack of money so it was posponed to this coming weekend. except that i have my orientation at wendys sunday morning, but who cares, i can go to it still drunk from the night before... except for the fact that i cant!!!! but thats all right, something will be figured out. i would love to bring some decatur kids up here for it. then you can see how i roll now. plus i dont wanna admit it but i miss people alot... but thats ok, because im gonna slowly move all of you to chicago... i really miss eric...

andrew came to my house, thats what brittany was planning, she was surprising me with an old friend. he came over and we all had a great time, he was supposed to only stay for an hour because he had something to do, but he stayed 2 days, he cracks me up...

so today i was quietly smoking, minding my own bussines when my roomate brittany runs up to me and starts laughing. so i ask her whats so funny and she says you will see, and it will make you cry, it could ruin your life, make your life so much better, you never know, its gonna happen tonight or tommorow night... there was more to it, but i dare not speak it... what ive gathered is that some decaturins are involved... which freaks me out because you decatur folk are some crazy motha fuckas... maybes shes just feeding on my already high levels of paranoia... or maybe im gonna die tonight, if anyone knows what this is about... please tell me, because from the looks of it, it might not be tonight...

o shit, im fucked up... it fucking sucks about hunter... i watched fear and loathing tonight, got drunk, got high, ate shrooms all in his memory...

today fuckin sucked...it was a hella shitty day, i got really pissed for a kinda good reason, i got let down by a good friend of mine... i met i guy i really want to bash his head in with a metal bat repeativly until way after he has taken his last pointless breathe... im still kinda pissed, the weather was fucking gay this morning, i really really dispise snow now, its ugly and fills you with a fake fucking feeling of happiness that doesnt last. nothinng good lasts i swear... im in such a bad mood, i didnt go to sleep until 10 this morning, and not because of something fun like drinking and having a good time, but because of a really annoying thing that spawned this entire death mood im in, and im ranting on but i dont fucking care, im bored and want some way to express myself, god there  are so many things bothering me right now it unexplainable...

i need to smoke!!! we are broke now, cigs are scarce. there is this girl who is paying me 50$ to draw her a pic of vash from trigun so she can get a tattoo of it. its a pretty sweet deal, her name is cat, from what i know... i think i did a really good job on it, and i think i have a way to put my art online, because bill ( my roomate) has a really good digital camera. i never called the girl who took my shirt... i kinda feel bad, but ive been busy trying to get that vash picture perfect so i can buy us all food and smokes and stuff.

so i went to an irish punk bar thingy and i was buying a beer and i was wearing my bondage shirt. some girl next to me wanted it so she said she would buy it. i really didnt want to sell it but she was really nice and cute, and im a sucker for a pretty face. so i told her to buy me a beer and give me her number. which is wierd because im suposed to be shy. her name is george, so im happy i made another friend. ummm... and thats about all that went on last night.
im here in chicago, there is a computer. ive made some friends. ate a tongue burritto... went to a polish market... and im going to this bar tonight. so im having a good time.

well well well... i got really trashed last night, because it was my last saturday night in town, things didnt work out as planned tho i wanted to have like a party so i can invite everyone i love but it couldnt work out that way, so i went to a milikin party and got shittay!! i went with burt, blair, eric, amanda, jarod, and annie, then we went back to the hotel room and smoked a lil bit o weezy, me and blair and burt stayed the night at the hotel and everyone else went home at like 5 in the morning, it was awesome. i dont think ive ever been that drunk/high. im leaving tom. morning to live in chicago with burt and all that jazz. and i dont know if thier will be a computer ther so this might be the last time i write in this thing for awile.
im kinda scared but itll be ok. so goodbye everyone, ill miss you all.
my cell phone number is 791-3570, it usually doesnt have very many mins, but i use it as a pager, burts number is 1815-549-6441, i dont know the house number tho, but get ahold of me someone, and we will make plans for you to come up to chicago and visit and stay for a little bit and go to parties and all of that wich is fun.

Does he kiss your eyelids in the morning when you start to raise your head? And does he sing to
you incessantly from the place between your bed and wall? Does he walk around all day at
school with his feet inside your shoes? Looking down every few steps to pretend he walks with
you. Does he know that place below your neck that is your favorite to be touched and does he cry
through broken sentences like I love you far too much? Does he lay awake listening to your
breath? Worried that you smoke too many cigarettes. Is he coughing now on a bathroom floor?
For every speck of tile there are a thousand more that you won't ever see but most hold inside
yourself eternally.

And the angel of the lord came unto me. Snatching me up from my place of slumber, and took me on high, and higher still until we moved through the spaces betwixt the air itself. And he brought me into a vast farmland of our own midwest. And as we descended, cries of impending doom arose from the soil. 

One thousand, nay, a million voices full of fear. And terror possessed me then. And I begged: "Angel of the lord, what are these tortured screams?" And the angel said unto me: "These are the cries of the carrots. The cries of the carrot. You see, reverend Maynard, tomorrow is harvest day, and to them, it is the holocaust." 

And I sprang from my slumber drenched in sweat with the tears of one million terrified brothers and roared: "Hear me now, I have seen the light. They have a consciousness! They have a life! They have a soul. Damn you! Let the rabbits wear glasses. Save our brothers. Can I get an amen. Can I get a haleluia. Thank you, Jesus."

i did a free sample tarot card reading online today, you only get to pick 3 cards and this is what i got. i was happy with the results. they were right on the money. http://www.tarot.com/tarot/index.php?

Three of Wands
Position: Love & Me
Main (positional) Meaning:
You and a potential love interest are prepared to take risks to explore new opportunities or enterprises.

The card in the Love & Me position touches on an aspect of how you perceive yourself with regard to possible intimacy in your life.

When the Three of Wands is in this position an adventure is about to be set in motion. This card represents the burning drive that compels a person to risk his or her worldly fortunes for a chance at greatness. Committed to a plan of action, you and a possible partner may be poised to gather resources for a step by step procedure. 

An enterprising spirit inspires you both to strike out in this new direction rather than stay with the status quo. Now you can confidently set out on this journey of exploration and hopefully, enrichment.


Page of Wands
Position: Situation
Main (positional) Meaning:
Change will escalate rapidly. Be quick to participate.

The card that lands in the Situation position refers to social or circumstantial factors which could be affecting your life at this time.

This card is traditionally entitled a Page, but in some modern decks as a Princess. When the Page of Wands is in this position, change is in the air. News may have been released about developments that could put stress on a potential relationship. 

This may be a good time to reaffirm the mutual goal before everyone hits the ground running. Be prepared for a change in hierarchy, a new set of policies, or even a new turn of events to come out of nowhere. Whatever it is, you are in a position to participate in the wave of the future. Change will escalate quickly. 

This is not necessarily a negative development, however, so do not let anyone think this is something to get upset or emotional about. The essential thing? Remember that your purpose is to respond, rather than retreat and wait.


Eight of Coins
Position: Challenges
Main (positional) Meaning:
Give yourself a reprieve from your intense striving. You may gather energy for a potential relationship at a later time.

The card that lands in the Challenges position refers to ways that you can turn obstacles into stepping stones.

The Eight of Coins in this position offers you a chance to render high quality work in a future relationship without becoming consumed by the process. Yes, by all means create beauty, but do remember to take breaks. Your intimacy may be rigorous, not just artistic and aesthetic. You need time off to pursue other activities, a social life and some diversions.

Refresh yourself. Take a break from your single-minded focus so you may return to your desired relationship with renewed energy, excitement, and longing. For optimal health, refrain from an "all or nothing" style. Pace yourself. Avoid burning the candle at both ends. This will benefit both you and your future love interest.
